 fairfax’s corporate objective is to achieve a high rate of return on invested capital and build longterm shareholder value fairfax seeks to differentiate itself by combining disciplined underwriting with the investment of its assets on a total return basis which fairfax believes provides aboveaverage returns over the longterm fairfax was founded in  by the present chairman and chief executive officer v prem watsa the company has been under present management since  and is headquartered in toronto canada its common shares are listed on the toronto stock exchange under the symbol ffh and in us dollars under the symbol ffhu fairfax’s insurance and reinsurance companies operate on a decentralized basis with autonomous management teams applying a focused underwriting strategy to their markets fairfax subsidiaries provide a full range of property and casualty products maintaining a diversified portfolio of risks across all classes of business geographic regions and types of insureds since  investments have been centrally managed for all of the fairfax group companies by hamblin watsa investment counsel ltd wwwhwicca a whollyowned subsidiary of fairfax hamblin watsa emphasizes a conservative value investment philosophy seeking to invest assets on a total return basis which includes realized and unrealized gains over the longterm   fairfax financial holdings limited global links legal notice site map login powered by q inc  fairfax  contact us corporate company profileguiding principlesglobal overviewfinancial track recordacquisition track recordinsurance and reinsurance companies adventalltrustasuransi magbic insurancebrit limitedbryte insurancecolonnade insurancecrum  forstereurolife erbfairfax brasilfairfirst insurancefalcon insurance hong kongfalcon insurance thailandfirst capitalgroup regulf insuranceicici lombardnorthbridgeodysseyrepacific insurancepolish reriverstonesingapore rethai rezenith national investment management hamblin watsa investment counsel board of di